---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import EnquiryForm from '../components/EnquiryForm.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="Pro City Laser Removal is a UK-wide specialist in laser cleaning for graffiti, heritage, fire damage, industrial, and paint removal. Learn about our team and approach."
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="text-sm text-neutral-mid mb-8">
      <ol class="flex gap-2">
        <li><a href="/" class="hover:text-neutral-dark transition-colors">Home</a></li>
        <li aria-hidden="true">›</li>
        <li aria-current="page" class="text-on-surface">About</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <header class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold text-neutral-dark mb-4">About Pro City Laser Removal</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-mid">
        We are a UK-wide specialist in laser cleaning — graffiti removal, heritage conservation,
        fire damage remediation, industrial cleaning, and paint removal. Every project is
        documented with before-and-after photography.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-dark mb-4">Company</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-neutral max-w-none text-on-surface">
        <p>
          Pro City Laser Removal provides specialist laser cleaning services to councils, heritage bodies,
          insurers, loss adjusters, and commercial contractors across the United Kingdom.
        </p>
        <p>
          Placeholder — company history and founding story to follow once confirmed with client.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-dark mb-4">Why laser cleaning</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-neutral max-w-none text-on-surface">
        <p>
          Laser cleaning is non-abrasive, chemical-free, and precise enough for the most sensitive
          substrates — including carved heritage stonework, polychrome surfaces, and irreplaceable
          masonry. It leaves no secondary waste stream and produces a cleaner, more controlled result
          than traditional sandblasting or chemical methods.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is not a preference — it is why Pro City chose laser as the primary method. The
          process carries less risk to the substrate, less regulatory burden on the client, and
          produces photographic evidence that meets the documentation requirements of councils,
          insurers, and heritage bodies.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-dark mb-4">Team</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-mid">Team profile to follow — owner name, background, and photograph to be supplied.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-dark mb-4">Insurance &amp; compliance</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-mid">
        Full public liability and employer's liability insurance is in place. RAMS and COSHH documentation
        are available on request — a requirement we regularly meet for councils, heritage bodies, and
        principal contractors.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3">
        <a href="/contact/" class="text-accent hover:underline text-sm">
          Request certificates or documentation
        </a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-dark mb-4">Sister company</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-mid">
        Pro City Laser Removal is part of the same group as{' '}
        <a
          href="https://www.procitypainters.co.uk"
          class="text-accent hover:underline"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          aria-label="Pro City Painters (opens in new tab)"
        >
          Pro City Painters
        </a>
        {' '}— a complementary service for clients who require both cleaning and redecoration under the same professional standards.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <EnquiryForm />
</Base>
